{
  "texts": [
    "Therefore, it is crucial to ensure that DL models are scalable and can handle the increasing amounts of data that will be generated in the future.",
    "Generalizability refers to the ability of a model to perform well on new, unseen data.",
    "In medical applications, generalizability is critical because it is essential that models can accurately predict outcomes for new patients.",
    "DL models are often criticized for their lack of generalizability, as they may perform well on the training dataset but struggle when presented with new data.",
    "Therefore, developing DL models that are generalizable to new patient populations and disease types is important."
  ]
}